  "_comment": "Comprehensive gfx942 SDPA-fwd shape set, deduplicated across representative LLM and unified-attention workloads: fp16/bf16, head_size in {64,128,256}, MHA + GQA{2,4,5,8}, decode/short-prefill/long-prefill regimes, batch 1-64, seqlen 1-8192; capped to a ~16GB fp32-reference memory budget so the sweep fits one MI300X. Groups are by regime. This benchmark is causal-only (the CK unified-attention kernel always applies a causal mask and has no non-causal mode), so non-causal prefill shapes are not included; decode (seqlen_q=1) attends to all keys, which the causal kernel computes correctly. The 'd256_disabled' group is OFF BY DEFAULT (head_size=256 has no tiled path on gfx942 -> scalar fallback: much slower than flash, fails correctness on some shapes, and stalls graph capture at S2048). Re-run with `--groups d256_disabled`.",
